quiz.text: Quantity I: Ratio of time taken by B to A is 3:1.They together complete the work in 12 days. Find how many days are required by B alone to complete the work. Quantity II: 12 men work for 6 hours a day to complete 460-units work in 240 days. Find how many days are required by 18 men complete to 140-unit work working 8 hours in a day. Quantity I < Quantity II > Quantity III

quiz.text: Number of boys in class A is 40. Number of girls in B is half of the number of boys in the same class. Ratio of girls in class A and class C is 10:9. Number of boys in D is equal to the number of girls in A. Number of boys and girls in class C is equal. Number of girls in D is equal to the number of boys in A. Total students in each class are equal i.e., 90. Quantity I: Total boys in class C and D are equal is what percent of the total boys in class A and B together?  Quantity II: Number of boys in class A and number of girls in class D together is what percent of the number of girls in class B and C together? Quantity III: Total number of boys in all classes together is what percent of total number of girls in all classes together?
options: Quantity I < Quantity II >Quantity III
Quantity I ≥ Quantity II< Quantity III
Quantity II ≥ Quantity I< Quantity III
Quantity I > Quantity II >Quantity III
Quantity I < Quantity II < Quantity III
